            "content": [
              {
                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are the latest updates for the London Underground as of early December 2025:\n\n1. **Northern Line**: No service between Archway and High Barnet/Mill Hill East after 5:30 AM on both December 6th and 7th. Also, no service between Charing Cross and Golders Green/High Barnet from 1:45 AM to 5:30 AM on the same dates [Time Out](https://www.timeout.com/london/news/london-travel-disruption-this-weekend-full-list-of-tube-and-train-closures-for-december-5-7-2025-120425).\n\n2. **Piccadilly Line**: No service between Acton Town and Uxbridge on December 6th and 7th. Metropolitan Line also closed between Harrow-on-the-Hill and Uxbridge on these dates. Replacement buses available [Time Out](https://www.timeout.com/london/news/london-travel-disruption-this-weekend-full-list-of-tube-and-train-closures-for-december-5-7-2025-120425).\n\n3. **Waterloo & City Line**: Closed on weekends, operates Monday to Friday [Traffic Delays](https://www.trafficdelays.co.uk/london-trains/).\n\nFor more detailed, real-time updates, you can check the official Transport for London website or use the TfL Go app [TfL](https://tfl.gov.uk/status-updates).",
